{
  "texts": [
    "Genes involved in lignin biosynthesis interact with nucleotidebinding leucine-rich repeat proteins to modulate plant defense [123].",
    "Hydroxycinnamic acid amides such as p-coumaroylagmatine, feruloylagmatine, p-coumaroylputrescine, and feruloylputrescine confer defense to the fungal pathogen Alternaria brassicicola in Arabidopsis thaliana [125].",
    "The phenolic aldehyde vanillin, a derivative of ferulic acid, hinders the growth of multiple bacterial species by dissipating ion gradients and thereby inhibiting respiration [126].",
    "The hydroxycinnamic acid amide clovamide indirectly inhibits the growth of three species of Phytophthora, including P. palmivora, in cacao [83].",
    "And lastly, caffeic acid and its derivatives both directly and indirectly inhibit many pathogens, among them P. palmivora and P. megakarya [86,127].The last of these compounds, caffeic acid, is particularly interesting because the gene responsible for catalyzing the reaction from caffeoyl shikimate to caffeic acid, TcCSE, displays consistent upregulation across all four populations (Fig. 4A)."
  ]
}